text: Has anyone used the ‘supported filter’ for converting to an integer? We can't get it to work in unixtimestamp data for hubDB… If so, do you know what the limit of number places there are, if there is one?

So I am noticing a RSS Feed validation error on HS blogs when using <http://www.feedvalidator.org/>
Anytime I place a HubSpot blogs RSS feed in it, it gives me `Server returned [Errno 1] _ssl.c:504: error:14077410:SSL routines:SSL23_GET_SERVER_HELLO:sslv3 alert handshake failure`
I've tested this on some diamond/platinum partner blog rss.xml urls and its giving the same thing. Yet when I test HubSpots, it validates correctly
